  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_5' aria-label=\" Mohit Suresh Harchandrai & Ors. versus Hindustan Organic Chemicals Limited pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('5','2025','2025_5_764_772','2025INSC812'); ><font size='4'> <strong>MOHIT SURESH HARCHANDRAI & ORS.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>HINDUSTAN ORGANIC CHEMICALS LIMITED </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 5 S.C.R. 764</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 812</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010004282025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : SANJAY KAROL<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, MANOJ MISRA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration The crux of the dispute is the &lsquo;per square foot rate&rsquo; at which the mesne profit is to be calculated in connection with Hindustan Organic Chemicals Ltd.&rsquo;s (HOCL) occupation, as &lsquo;tenant&rsquo;. The High Court held that application of uniform rate of the rate of interest payable at 8% p.a. would be appropriate in the facts and circumstances of the present case. Headnotes&dagger; Mesne Profit &ndash; Calculation of &ndash; The tenant originally entered into the demised premises and 2nd floor thereof, totalling 7825 Sq.ft built-up area, as a<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 06-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 7188/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('5','2025','2025_5_764_772','2025INSC812','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>